doc.title: Eurommercial 1H25: solid operating trends, guidance upgraded
doc.source_uri: 2025-08-28/Eurocommercial 1H25 solid operating trends guidance upgraded Eurocommercial 1H25 solid operating trends guidance upgrade_2025-08-28

passages.text: Property/Real Estate

**Bernstein view.** Eurommercial reported continuously solid operating trends alongside valuation recovery in 1H25. 2025 guidance of €2.40-€2.45 direct investment result/share was upgraded to the upper end, a positive start to 2025 overall. The call is at 10am BST Friday the 29th (link).

**Earnings guidance uplifted.** Direct investment result per share of €1.25 (+0.9% yoy) came slightly below our estimates. This puts Eurommercial in a good position to reach its FY25 guidance that was upgraded to the upper end of the range of €2.40-€2.45. Our estimate/BBG cons. of €2.44 is in line.

**Rental growth continued, but uplifts have slowed.** LFL rental growth of +3.0% remained solid (1Q:+3.0%). Italy outperformed at +3.5% (1Q:+3.4%) as did Belgium at +3.2%, the latter strengthening through 2Q (1Q:+1.9%). France and Sweden followed at +2.7% and +2.3%, respectively. Rental uplifts were +2.9% ahead of indexation but slowing on prior levels (1Q:+3.8%), higher in Italy (+8.2%) and Belgium (+7.9%) (although both weakened vs 1Q at +10.7% and +4.0%, respectively) while Sweden turned marginally negative (-0.4%; 1Q:+0.2%). France continued its negative trajectory (-1.2%; in line with 1Q) due to the re-letting of units at lower rents to attract strong brands.

**Robust footfall and retailer sales growth, skewed towards 2Q on calendar effects.** Retail sales LFL rose +2.6% yoy for 1H (2Q:+4.9%,1Q:+2.0% yoy) supported by recently renovate projects at Woluwe and Carosello. Belgium saw 9.8%, the highest of the group. Italy and France saw +2.2% and Sweden +1.3% for 1H25. Footfall rose 0.5% over 1H (2Q:+2.2%). EPRA vacancy notched 0.0bp lower over 1H to 1.2% (-30bp over 2Q), declining across all regions except Belgium, which saw a 30bp increase over 1H).

**Property value-growth supported by Italy.** LFL values rose +1.3% over 1H25. By region, Italy saw the strongest growth of +2.1%. LFL revaluation movements for France (+0.9%), Belgium (+0.7%) and Sweden (+0.3%). EPRA NTA notched 0.8% lower over 1H to €41.46,0.5% ahead of our estimate. Prop. consol. LTV declined 80bp vs FY24 to 40.5% while EPRA LTV increased 1pp to 43.8% due to an uptick in net payables.
**Three new projects added.** Rememberinging projects were launched in Italy at Collestrada,I Gigli, and CremonaPO to refine market leadership.

We calculate our €30 PT using a 10- year DCF valuation with an average WACC of \(7.5\%\) and a long- term growth rate of \(1.8\%\) (based on country- weighted average long- term inflation forecasts with a 10bp discount applied). Our DCF valuation is based on our estimates of net operating profit after tax adjusted for net acquisitions/disposals and capex discounted by WACC to one- year forward. We deduct the market value of net debt and derivatives (including hybrids classified as equity, where applicable) and minority interests.
Upside - Higher growth than expected in asset values; higher than expected rental growth as offline retail sales growth is strong.
Downside - Higher for longer interest rate environment. Declines in asset value that endanger balance sheet. Consumer recession or faster online penetration.
